# GDS accessibility — mandatory for UI work

When you **create or materially change React UI** (`.tsx` / `.jsx`):

1. **Follow the Accessibility section** in `node_modules/@gds-vero/react/GDS_FOR_LLM_AGENTS.md` (WCAG 2.1 AA).
2. **Complete the “Accessibility review (mandatory for agents)” checklist** in that file before finishing. Fix violations in code.
3. **Run `npm run lint` or `pnpm lint`** and fix all `jsx-a11y/*` errors on touched files.
4. **Report accessibility** under **Accessibility** in the mandatory **Delivery audit report** — do not skip the full audit report.

Common fixes: `aria-label` on icon-only buttons, `Field.Label` + `Field.ErrorText`, `GDSHeading as="h*"`, `aria-hidden` on decorative icons.

Human reference: https://github.com/tomiputto/gds-vero#readmeaccessibility
